      "focusDirectory": "",
      "colorMode": "fileTypes"
    },
    {
      "id": "step-2-dual-stack",
      "title": "Dual-Stack Layout",
      "description": "The repo splits cleanly along stack lines. The Rust API owns auth, domain logic, and the database. The frontend is a thin client that calls the API. A workspace manifest and a top-level build contract glue the two halves together.",
