      "id": "step-4-auth",
      "title": "Authentication (P1)",
      "description": "Authentication lives entirely in the backend — the frontend has no auth layer of its own. The Google OAuth flow handles sign-in, signed Postgres-backed sessions keep users logged in, and a request extractor makes the current user available to handlers. The frontend sign-in button simply redirects into the backend flow.",
